<% flash.each do |key, message| %>
  <div class="alert alert-dismissible custom-alert <%= key.to_s == 'alert' ? 'alert-danger' : 'alert-success' %>" role="alert">
    <%= message %>
    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="alert" aria-label="Close"></button>
  </div>
<% end %>

<div class="container-fluid d-flex flex-grow gap-5">
  <div class="about-section w-50">
    <h2>Hospital Management System <span width="100px">+<span> </h2>
    <%= image_tag 'images/hospital.jpg', class: "img-fluid rounded", alt: "..alt image." %>
    <p class="my-4 font-italic font-weight-bold text-justify" style="word-spacing: 10px">
      A hospital management application is a software system designed to streamline and enhance various administrative and operational tasks within a healthcare facility. This application serves as a centralized platform for managing different aspects of hospital operations, including patient records, appointments, staff scheduling, billing, inventory management, and more.

      One of the primary features of a hospital management application is patient management. It allows healthcare providers to maintain comprehensive electronic health records (EHR) for each patient, including medical history, diagnoses, treatment plans, and medication records. This digital record system improves the efficiency of data retrieval, reduces paperwork, and enables better collaboration among healthcare professionals.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="login-section w-50">
    <div class="login-form">
      <%= form_with url: login_path do |f| %>
        <h1>Login Here:</h1>

        <div class="form-group">
          <%= f.label :email %>
          <%= f.email_field :email, class: 'form-control', required: true %>
        </div>

        <div class="form-group">
          <%= f.label :password %>
          <%= f.password_field :password, class: 'form-control', required: true %>
          <div id="emailHelp" class="form-text">We'll never share your email with anyone else.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-group">
          <%= f.submit 'Login', class: 'btn btn-success' %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
      
      <%= link_to 'Forgot Password', forgot_password_path %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
